H O U S E R E S O L U T I O N
AMENDING THE RULES OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES FOR THE YEARS
2023 AND 2024
Introduced By: Representatives McGaw, Boylan, Spears, Carson, Fogarty, Kislak,
Cotter, Cortvriend, Ajello, and Speakman
Date Introduced: January 10, 2025
Referred To: House Rules
1 RESOLVED, that the rules of the House of Representatives adopted by the House of
2 Representatives at its January session, A.D., 2023, entitled “House Resolution Adopting Rules of
3 the House of Representatives for the years 2023 and 2024,” be and the same is hereby amended
4 by adding the following new rule thereto:
5 (49) Recognizing the Importance of Leading by Example.
6 (a) The following items shall not be permitted on the floor of the House or in any spaces
7 utilized for House proceedings except when required for safety, health, or emergency situations:
8 (1) Plastic plates;
9 (2) Plastic cutlery;
10 (3) Plastic straws;
11 (4) Plastic beverage containers;
12 (5) Single-use plastic drinkware; and
13 (6) Food or beverage containers composed in whole or in part of polystyrene foam.
